gemini-1.5-pro.ocr_text:
GREAT SMOKY MOUNTAINS NATIONAL PARK
GSMNP10735

Diapensiaceae Plants of Tennessee
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

Tennessee : Sevier County
35.65374° Latitude -83.54858° Longitude 3130ft. Elevation
Quadrangle: Gatlinburg West Prong Little River Watershed
T. 11S. R. 72E. Sect. 3

The Great Smoky Mountains National Park. Along the Sugarland Mountain Trail starting at Fighting Creek Gap. Small open areas at the junction of Fighting Creek Gap & the Rough Creek Trail. At Huskey Gap. Coordinate Datum: WGS84/NAD83.

Small open areas with *Acer rubrum* (dominant), *Magnolia fraseri*, *Oxydendrum arboreum*, *Pinus rigida*, *Quercus alba*, *Q. prinus*, *Sassafras albidum*, *Acer pensylvanicum*, *Castanea dentata*, *Gaylussacia ursina*, *Kalmia latifolia*, *Pyrularia pubera*, *Rhododendron maximum*, *Rubus canadensis*, *Dennstaedtia punctiloba*, *Chrysopsis mariana*, *Eurybia divaricata*, etc.

CAT. NO.
GRSM 113862 (handwritten)

595 Connie Carroll-Cunningham, Grant Cunningham & Loy R. Phillippe
16 October 2007

Illinois Natural History Survey (ILLS)

SERNEC Digitization Project - Tennessee Herbarium Consortium


*Galax urceolata*
